From: Borislav Petkov <borislav.petkov@amd.com>
Date: Tue, 13 Sep 2011 15:23:21 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 25/31] x86, mce: Enable MCA support by default

commit e57dbaf77f372ac461b5b0b353c65efae9739a00	upstream

MCA is the basic support for hardware error logging and reporting, and
it is majorly unwise to run without it so enable machine check software
support by default on x86.

Signed-off-by: Borislav Petkov <borislav.petkov@amd.com>
Acked-by: Tony Luck <tony.luck@intel.com>
---
 arch/x86/Kconfig |    1 +
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/arch/x86/Kconfig b/arch/x86/Kconfig
index 055beee..5017acc 100644
--- a/arch/x86/Kconfig
+++ b/arch/x86/Kconfig
@@ -874,6 +874,7 @@ config X86_REROUTE_FOR_BROKEN_BOOT_IRQS
 
 config X86_MCE
 	bool "Machine Check / overheating reporting"
+	default y
 	---help---
 	  Machine Check support allows the processor to notify the
 	  kernel if it detects a problem (e.g. overheating, data corruption).
